CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published In Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, page A14, reads: "Gay Northeasterners Plan Confab - Members of the Pittsburgh chapter of the Gay Northeasterners (there are seven chapters in all) are ready for the national gathering which will take over the social scene May 30-June 1. Glittering plans are in order for the delegates and members who make Pittsburgh the focal point for fun and festivity that important week-end. Pictured are chairmen of the various committees. Left to right, front row: Mmes. Alyce Woodruff, Mary McEinheimer, Julia Gaines, Helen Prattis and Virginia Carter Lowe. Second row: Mmes. Marian Holmes, Eloise Page and Margaret Jane Smith. Top row: Mmes. Easter Little, Thelma Allen and Elizabeth Henderson. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Chapter of the Gay Northeasterners members: unknown, Virginia Carter Lowe, Margaret Jane Smith, and Eloise Page, standing behind table with sterling silver tea set at the Greene Hearth
